Class AggregableMatchingRule<RecordType extends Matchable,SchemaElementType extends Matchable>

  • java.lang.Object

    Direct Known Subclasses:
    IdentityMatchingRule, VotingMatchingRule

    public abstract class AggregableMatchingRule<RecordType extends Matchable,SchemaElementType extends Matchable>
extends MatchingRule<RecordType,SchemaElementType>
implements RecordKeyValueMapper<Pair<RecordType,RecordType>,Correspondence<RecordType,SchemaElementType>,Correspondence<RecordType,SchemaElementType>>
    A matching rule that specifies how correspondences are grouped for aggregation. If a correspondence has a score below finalThreshold, its score is set to 0.0 instead of removing it to allow for correct aggregation of the scores in a followin step (i.e. average score)
    Author:
    Oliver Lehmberg (oli@dwslab.de)
